      <tr>
        <td bgcolor='black' valign=top width='100' nowrap><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'><b>Zothar</b></font></td>
        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> IM a lv 52 Nec looking for a TOFS guide. I have used the search function but it did not come up with anything usefull.. </P><P>How far can I get in here? and what should I camp? Tactics?  I have a lot of crappy gear that i need to replace and this seems to be nice time to grab some xp and loot.</P><P>Zothar Darksoul<BR>52 Nec TZ</font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Xararsis</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Ok first off i'd like to scold you and say you should've came here at 51 :P.  This place is a necro's paradise.  First and foremost I think that you should go to <a href="http://www.eqatlas.com" target="_blank">www.eqatlas.com</a> and print out a map of TOFS.  Then you should go and check out allakhazam.com for the key mobs on each floor that allow you to reach the next one.  Tips for you from a necro veteran of this zone about dyingare:</P><P>- Bind yourself at the gnoll outpost just outside TOFS, you will thank me once you die here.<BR>- Keep your cool when you die.... sure it totally sucks, but there is usually a cleric around the area that can rez you.  <BR>- If you die on a floor higher then lvl 2 or 3 the best thing to do is from IC run to GD wizzie portal and get a coffin from the bazaar in luclin.  </P><P>Some key mobs that drop loot that you might consider worthwhile are:<BR>-The angry librarian on the 2nd floor.  She drops "Students Homework" and "Teacher's Sylabus" both are range slot items and you'll prolly find the homework better.  This mob also drops the key to the next floor and also is spawned by basically killing off every ghost on the floor (at 52 that poses absolutly no prob).<BR>-Shadowbones on the 3rd drop bonechips just an FYI :).<BR>- 4th Floor Cara Omica drops a "Embalmers Skinning Knife" (nice cash if you get a buyer), as well as a "Sorcerors Bowl".  The bowl serves as a very nice handheld item for any necro with +50hp and 7int it's very nice indeed.  Next section I will tell you the dangers and ph's to get Cara.<BR>- 5th floor Nosja drops an incredible ring called the "Diamond Wedding Band."  Look the stats up on this one it's very nice and all the mobs from the entrance point to the wedding area are like lvl 35.</P><P>Very important!! Once you get all your keys and even if you don't, whenever you're traveling through the 4th floor make sure you have gather shadows on and con EVERY mummy you see!!!! Everything on this floor CAN'T see invis except for one mummy.  The rest of the mummies also can't see through invis it's just one and he's not always around or up.  If you happen to come across this mummy while you're traveling through the floor by god say a prayer and hope to god you make it out alive.  Typically once he sees you he will aggro you then every shadow in the zone will proceed to cast their 200dd's on you and you will die faster then a snake on a newbie ground :).  You will see what I mean once you get up there.</P><P>Place for you to hunt in TOFS from 52 until you ding 54 is:<BR>The Ice Shadows on the floor 6a.  These guys are super easy as long as you don't let their dots kick the crap outta your pet. Tactics for hunting these guys are:<BR>-Pull with shackle of bone (60% undead slow) makes the fight significantly easier.<BR>-If after you cast the spell and they stay and begin to cast a dot/dd depending on the casting time on the spell cast ST on it so he doesn't get it off. You will know after a while what times to use ST or not depending on what spell eh tries to hit you with.<BR>-After you shackle him and he runs at you run him to your parked pet outside the room in the hall somewhere and allow your pet to beat on him.  Make sure you deal out about 2 banish undeads each fight to help your pet out.<BR>-If your pet gets lower then say 60hp you might wanna BOD the mob and then pact your pet.  Also if your pet gets dot'ed he will lose hps faster so make sure you're watching him.</P><P>Things to look out for hunting ice shades!<BR>-If you see a special ice shadow that looks more like a spectre and has a pet pull him CAREFULLY with ST!  AFter that his pet will come after you.  Let your pet rip his apart.  By then ST will basically have worn off and you do the above like it was any other pull, but if you don't pull this guy with ST he will give you a very hard time because he can make the other shades around him assist.  It's weird they will assist him when he gets pulled but not their other friends lol.  You might be wondering what the hell they put him in for anyways.  The answer to that is he is the PH for Vhalsera the mob on 6b that drops the key to 7, but for exp hunting you will be nowhere near 6b.<BR>-Also very important on the EQATLAS map it will say on 6a a "Trap Area."  This is an ice shade camping spot as well as the other one very close to this one, BUT and it's a big but stay out of the room altogether!  This means pull the mobs from the steps and wait until they get there don't venture out to the floor.  There is a trap once you step out onto the floor far enough.  A statue casts a 450 or so DD that can really be a kick in the ass!</P><P><BR>Ok this is my general guide on this zone I truly hope you read it all and enjoyed it.  I didn't look over this after I finished it so if something was unclear please reply back asking me about it.  Also if you have other questions regarding TOFS please just reply also.  I know this zone seems very dangerous, but once you know the tough parts it truly is a breeze and a very fun zone.  The ice shades by the way are insane exp and drop up to 11pp a kill on top of weapons, spells, and crystalized shadows.  Well I think that is it I hope this helps.</P><P>-Xararsis Shadowbearer-<BR>(54th Iksar Heretic)</font></td>
