 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Mercyy</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Hi,</P><P>I am elvel 33 and soloed a fair bit in 32 on the first floor.  I would recommend IVUing up a bit and wandering around just to get a feel for the mobs.  There are a few things you can do:</P><P>-Left of the slippery hole, there is a hallway.  There is a room off of this hallway with three skels.  This room can be broken (with a fair amount of luck) and camped for some decent exp.  I actually stayed there a bit to resupply on bonechips while getting exp.  In that same hallway is a fourth lone skellie.  Throw him in for extra exp once you have the three in the room sorted out.</P><P>Alternatively... the lesser ice shades can be (with some playing around) single pulled.  Once they get to the entrance hallway, just fear them , no need to darkness.  They will run into the entry mirror and just keep running in place while pet beats on them.  I slowed them, so that they would not butcher me when fear broke.  Also, if you get an add or two, just keep them feared too.  They will all sit there getting beat on quite happily.</P><P>Only major problem you will run into at 32 is the key holder.  He is an enraged something or other (whatever the drolvarg things are... tend not to hunt those fellows.. shadow beasts?).  He would probably be able to disrupt your camp.  He spawns after you`ve killed one of the normal mobs (any mob anywhere can trigger him).</P><P>Cheers</P><P>Mercyy Less<BR>Level 32 Necromancer,<BR>Test<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=149969" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=149969</a></font></td>
